<section id="fb1">
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000">1. <b>a dip</b>: A dip is a slight and temporary fall in an otherwise stable trend.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb2">
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000">2. <b>a peak</b>: The figures reach their highest point and then fall.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb3">
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000">3. <b>a sharp rise</b>: The figures suddenly begin a dramatic rise.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb4">
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000">4. <b>a slight drop</b>: The figures fall a little and then remain stable.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb5">
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000">5. <b>a steady downward trend</b>: The figures don't fall dramatically, but there is a slight, continuous fall.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb6">
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000">6. <b>an overall upward trend</b>: Although there may be some very slight falls occasionally, generally the figures rise steadily throughout the time shown in the graph.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb7">
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000">7. <b>to fluctuate</b>: The figures are continuously changing around the same point.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb8">
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000">8. <b>to plunge</b>: The figures suddenly take a very large fall.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb9">
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000">9. <b>to reach a plateau</b>: In the beginning there is an upward trend, but then the increase falls off and the figures remain stable.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb10">
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000">10. <b>to remain stable</b>: There is no significant change in the figures.</font>
  </p>
</section>

